  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Our hypothesis is that intensive training with positive biofeedback may enhance postural
      control and stability in Parkinson's disease patients and in elderly fallers.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is to treat Parkinson's patients and elderly fallers. The intervention
      is intensive training with Biofeedback to try to correct stooped posture, and to improve
      stability in standing and in walking.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
